The index, which gauges manufacturing activity in Africa’s most industrialised economy, fell to 45.7 in August from 52.1 in July, falling below the 50-point mark separating contraction from expansion. All of the five major subcomponents in the index were below the neutral 50-point mark. “Respondents continued to be fairly downbeat about exports for a third straight month, while domestic demand likely also weighed on orders,” Absa said in a statement.

--Reuters--